p: The black soldier fly larva is a nutrient-rich feed source: Values regarding the protein and fat content obtained in the present study for a defatted larva meal are in line with data retrieved from the literature for this type of product [ 32]. Even if, with age, feed efficiency and laying performance of quails are expected to decline progressively, overall results of laying quails of the present study were satisfactory, considering that they had a feed efficiency of 3.47, which was better than the value of 3.59 recorded in 9-week-old laying Japanese quails [ 33].
